    "## Modelsetup"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook explains the MultiRegionWindForecastModel class to model the wind in different regions (e.g. for the pricing of greeen PPA). \n",
    "\n",
    "For this we assume that we have given $n$ artificial regions...\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "Let us denote by $q_i(t,T)$ the wind forecast at time $t$ for future time $T$  in region $i$ (as  percentage of maximal capacity for this region) by\n",
    "$$\n",
    "q_i(t,T) = E\\left[f\\left(f^{-1}(q_i(0,T)) + X^i_T-X_0^i\\right)\\mid X^i_t\\right]\n",
    "$$\n",
    "where $f$ is an invertible sigmoid function such as the logistic or smoothstep function and $X_t$ a stochastic process. We define $\\phi^i(T):= f^{-1}(q_i(0,T))-X^i_0$ and get\n",
    "$$\n",
    "q_i(t,T) = E\\left[f\\left(\\phi^i(T) + X^i_T\\right)\\mid X^i_t\\right]\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-05-09T05:16:54.179720Z",
     "start_time": "2023-05-09T05:16:54.134374Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# setup \n",
    "wind_region_model = {}\n",
    "vols = [1.0,3.0,6.0]\n",
    "mean_reversion_speed = [0.5,2.0,6.0]\n",
    "capacities = [10_000.0, 120_000.0, 75_000.0]\n",
    "rnd_weights = [ [0.8,0.2],\n",
    "               [0.8,0.2],\n",
    "               [0.8,0.2]\n",
    "              ]\n",
    "np.random.seed(42)\n",
    "regions = []\n",
    "for i in range(len(vols)):\n",
    "    model = WindPowerForecastModel(region='Region_' + str(i), \n",
    "                                            speed_of_mean_reversion=mean_reversion_speed[i],\n",
    "                                            volatility=vols[i])\n",
    "    regions.append(MultiRegionWindForecastModel.Region( \n",
    "                                    model,\n",
    "                                    capacity=capacities[i],\n",
    "                                    rnd_weights=rnd_weights[i]\n",
    "                                ) )\n",
    "wind = MultiRegionWindForecastModel('Wind_Germany', regions)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "After setting up three regions we just simulate the weather forecast over the next ten days for the following four hours."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {
    "ExecuteTime": {
     "end_time": "2023-05-09T05:16:54.502573Z",
     "start_time": "2023-05-09T05:16:54.180891Z"
    }
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n_sims = 10_000\n",
    "days = 10 # number of days\n",
    "timegrid = np.linspace(0.0, days*1.0/365.0, days*24) # simulation time grid\n",
    "forward_expiries = [timegrid[-1] + i/(365.0*24.0) for i in range(4)] # time points for the forwards\n",
    "rnd = np.random.normal(size=wind.rnd_shape(n_sims, timegrid.shape[0]))\n",
    "results = wind.simulate(timegrid, rnd, expiries=forward_expiries, \n",
    "                                       initial_forecasts={'Region_0': [0.7, 0.7,0.6,0.5],\n",
    "                                                          'Region_1': [0.75, 0.6, 0.5, 0.5],\n",
    "                                                         'Region_2': [0.8, 0.6, 0.5, 0.5]} # initial forecast values for the repsective 4 hours \n",
    "                               )"
   ]
